@galerieslafayette in Paris is an ornate glass-domed department store featuring everything from various food options and souvenirs to collections from some of the most well-known designers. 

The Galeries Lafayette Rooftop is an observation deck located on the 8th floor with a gorgeous view of the city, typically open from 10am - 8:30pm. It’s accessible by both elevator and escalators, and is completely free of charge. 

#galerieslafayette #parissunset #parisrooftops #parisnight #parisiannights #parisnights #toitsdeparis #parisfrance #parisblogger

Dined at one of the most iconic Parisian restaurants, Le Train Bleu, located inside of the Gare de Lyon train station // wearing @shopsugarlips #sugarlipsxme 

Established in 1900, this Michelin star restaurant was designated a French national heritage site in 1972. The atmosphere feels like you’ve traveled back in time and the dining room displays 41 beautiful murals and paintings of different French regions. 

Delicious classic gourmet French dishes are served every day during lunch (11am-2:30pm) and dinner (7-10:30pm). It’s an experience well worth having while in Paris, just make sure to book a reservation in advance! 

#letrainbleu #garedelyon #parisrestaurant #pariscity #parisianlifestyle #paris #parisvibes #parisrestaurants #shopsugarlips

A day exploring Montmartre and Sacré Cœur ☕️🥖🎶🫶🏼

Montmartre is a beautiful area in Paris, rich with history and full of cobblestone streets, ivy-clad houses, vintage stores, and quaint restaurants. From Monet to Van Gogh to Picasso, it’s been a home and inspiration to many famous inhabitants. 

Located in the 18th arrondissement, Montmartre is easily accessible from the heart of Paris by a quick car or metro ride. You could easily spend a day here roaming through the streets and exploring popular spots like the Wall of Love, La Maison Rose, Moulin Rouge, and Place du Tertre (a cafe-lined square filled with artists painting scenery and portraits). 

One of the most iconic monuments in Paris is the Basilica of Sacré Cœur, a Roman Catholic church first opened in 1875. Sitting atop the Butte Montmartre, it has one of the most beautiful panoramic views of the entire city. Entry into Sacré Cœur is free for visitors, just be prepared to encounter busy crowds, as well as local vendors and buskers.

Until next time, Canada 🇨🇦 save this list for your next Lake Louise trip of things to know before you go

📍 Lake Louise is located in Banff National Park in the Canadian Rockies, about 2 hours from Calgary International Airport and 40 minutes from the town of Banff. 
🚌 On-site paid parking fills up quickly and may be shut down during certain parts of the year. Parks Canada has a bus service available from the Lake Louise Ski Resort that you can reserve online in advance. 
🚣‍♀️ Popular activities include renting a canoe from the dock, kayaking, or hiking. Visitors can also enjoy skiing, ice skating, and sleigh rides during the months the lake is frozen over. 
🏨 Fairmont Chateau Lake Louise is the perfect nearby hotel to stay at or grab food and drinks while visiting. Other lodging options are also available in the area or in neighboring towns like Banff and Canmore. 
🏔️ The water color is caused by fine rock dust in the glacial melt that trickles down to the lake. The sun reflects off these particles, refracting light and creating the turquoise color.

The castle up on the hill ✨ Located along the California coast right between Los Angeles and San Francisco, Hearst Castle boasts an impressive 165 rooms and 123 acres of gardens, terraces, pools, and walkways. 

Construction was carried out from 1919 - 1947 by architect Julia Morgan, the first woman to hold a title at the Paris School of Fine Arts. It was commissioned by press tycoon William Randolph Hearst, who was the inspiration for Orson Wells' infamous 1941 movie, Citizen Kane.

The castle was the site of countless old Hollywood parties with guests including Winston Churchill, Cary Grant, and Charlie Chaplin, and would cost $700 million to build today. It’s also filled with an impressive collection of art and artifacts dating as far back as ancient Egypt. 

The wider estate including 82,000 acres of land that’s home to many animals from the old Hearst Castle Zoo, including zebras (sadly, I didn’t see any while I was there).

Hearst Castle is now the most visited California state historical monument and is the perfect California road trip stop. The only way to visit the estate is through a tour, so make sure you book one before going.

A perfect afternoon at The Empress 🥂✨ The Fairmont Empress hotel first opened in 1908 and was named after Queen Victoria. The city of Victoria Canada actually grew around this stunning luxury hotel, which has been at the center of the city's social and business gatherings since opening.

Designated a National Historic Site of Canada in 1981, the property has had over $100 million in restorations throughout the years - most notably on its iconic Lobby Lounge, where afternoon tea is served. This Fairmont hotel was named one of the 10 Best Tea Experiences in the World by Condé Nast, with prices starting at $95 CAD per person.

It has also made the list of the 21 Most Iconic Hotels in the World and was named the Best Historic Hotel in the Americas in 2020. Famous guests have included Winston Churchill, John Wayne, Shirley Temple, Katharine Hepburn, John Travolta, and the British Royal family.

📍  Brentwood Bay Resort BC Canada: This luxurious boutique resort was one of the most relaxing places I’ve ever been to. Each room has a fireplace and jacuzzi tub, and the grounds have a spa, pool, jacuzzi, fine dining restaurant, and more. We took full advantage of the gorgeous views from our patio and ordered room service for every meal. 

Brentwood Bay is a small coastal village located on Vancouver Island in British Columbia Canada, just a short drive north of Victoria. It's best known for the famous Butchart Gardens and Victoria Butterfly Gardens, as well as the small resort town feel and numerous marinas. From Vancouver International Airport, it's about a three hour journey, including a ferry that's accessible with a car or as a foot passenger.

one of the most challenging, but also one of the most exciting, rewarding, and fulfilling years yet 🤍 2024, I’m ready for you 

2023 recap #reelinspiration #recap #2023recap #recaptrend #yearinreview

I was feeling creative so I made a little 2023 recap collage as I was reflecting on this past year 📸🎨📰 (as a perfectionist, this took way too long to make - but it was a lot of fun to do) 

This year was full of fun trips, weddings, festivals, influencer events, brunches, picnics, engagements, birthdays, holidays, and other celebrations. I traveled to around 100 cities across 12 states/provinces/prefectures throughout 3 countries, spending almost 3 months away from home (shoutout to @googlemaps for the info). 

I also had lows like getting laid off and a difficult 8 month long recovery for my ankle (turned foot) injury. But, I also spent a lot of time getting stronger in physical therapy, worked with some amazing brands/clients, and had my highest paid Instagram campaign ever. 

Thank you to everyone who made this year so incredible (sorry I couldn’t tag you all). I’m so excited for a new year refresh and have so much I want to accomplish in 2024.

Last night, my mom and I were invited to the Hallmark Channel x Us Weekly premiere for the second season of The Way Home 🎬✨🍿 #HallmarkPartner

This multigenerational fantasy drama explores the dynamic relationships between mother, daughter, and grandmother, as they uncover shocking truths that will impact all of their lives. They embark on an enlightening, surprising journey none of them could have imagined, with their gift of time travel. 

We had so much fun walking the red carpet, chatting with the stars of the show, enjoying yummy snacks and drinks, making new friends with the other mother and daughter duos, and taking tons of photos. Then, we headed inside for a Q&A with the actors and a screening of the first episode of season two. 

I can’t wait to watch the rest of the season and enjoy all the goodies they sent us home with! Season 2 of #TheWayHome premieres this Sunday, January 21st at 9/8c on #HallmarkChannel, starring @chy_leigh, @sadie_snow, @evanmwilliams, & #andiemacdowell
